'''Beckham World of Sport''' is a [[Association football|soccer]] academy (the [[David Beckham Academy]]), a sports center, and a football stadium<ref name="The Official David Beckham Website">{{cite news|url=http://www.davidbeckham.com/newsarticle.php?id=200&lastpage=5 |title=David’s World of Sport |publisher=The Official David Beckham Website|date=January 29, 2008|accessdate=June 12, 2009 }} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref> for professional players and for children which is being built<ref name="Cabo sao Roque to be released early 2009 Brazils most prestigious resort">{{cite news |url=http://www.internationalpropertyestates.com/page/cabo-sao-roque-brazil-real-estate-natal |title=Cabo sao Roque to be released in early 2009: Brazil's most prestigious resort |publisher=International Proprerty Estates |date=January 29, 2008 |accessdate=June 12, 2009 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20100720202945/http://www.internationalpropertyestates.com/page/cabo-sao-roque-brazil-real-estate-natal |archive-date=2010-07-20 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> at the [[Cape São Roque]] in the city of [[Natal, Rio Grande do Norte|Natal]], capital of the state of [[Rio Grande do Norte]] in [[Brazil]].

The complex is sponsored by the player [[David Beckham]] who visited Natal in January 2008 to launch the project.<ref name="Beckham: 'Não vou ensinar aos brasileiros'">{{cite news|url=http://globoesporte.globo.com/ESP/Noticia/Motor/0,,MUL278864-1311,00.html |title=Beckham: 'Não vou ensinar aos brasileiros' |language=Portuguese|publisher=Globoesporte.com|date=January 29, 2008|accessdate=June 12, 2009 }}</ref>

A [[resort]] called "Cabo São Roque" is being built along with the World of Sport.

