{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Cheam Sports Ground | nickname = | country = England | image = | location = [[Sutton, London|Sutton]], [[London]] | establishment = 1858 | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 1969 | club1 = [[Surrey County Cricket Club|Surrey]] | date = 29 August | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/779.html Ground profile }}
'''Cheam Road''' is a [[cricket]] ground in [[Sutton, London|Sutton]], [[London]] (formerly [[Surrey]]). The first recorded match on the ground was in 1940, when Sutton United Tramps played [[London Counties cricket team|London Counties]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/779_misc.html Other matches played on Cheam Road]</ref>
The ground held a single match in the 1955 [[Minor Counties Championship]] when the Surrey Second XI played the [[Warwickshire County Cricket Club|Warwickshire Second XI]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/779_minc.html Minor Counties Championship Matches played on Cheam Road]</ref> More recently, the ground has held Surrey Second XI matches in the [[Second XI Championship]] and the Second XI Trophy.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/779_sec.html Second XI Championship Matches played on Cheam Road]</ref><ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/779_set.html Second XI Trophy Matches played on Cheam Road]</ref>
[[Surrey County Cricket Club|Surrey]] played a single [[List-A cricket|List-A]] match against [[Derbyshire County Cricket Club|Derbyshire]] at Cheam Road in the 1969 [[Player's County League]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/779_a.html List-A Matches played on Cheam Road]</ref>
In local domestic cricket, Cheam Road is the home ground of [[Sutton Cricket Club]]<ref>[http://www.suttoncricketclub.com/page_332342.html Sutton Cricket Club] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110621232200/http://www.suttoncricketclub.com/page_332342.html |date=June 21, 2011 }}</ref> who play in the [[Surrey Premier League]]. Historically the cricket ground was part of the Lower Cheam House Estate and was donated to the cricket club. Having gone without a [[cricket pavilion|pavilion]] since 1858, the club bought the old waiting room at [[Sutton railway station (London)|Sutton railway station]] and installed it at the ground. In 1906 a wooden pavilion was built, but this was destroyed during [[The Blitz]]. A replacement pavilion was constructed in 1955.
