'''Colburn Park''' is a [[ballpark]] located in [[Newark, New York]], USA. It is home to the Newark Pilots (2011-present) of the [[Perfect Game Collegiate Baseball League]] and was the home for the [[Newark Co-Pilots]] (1968-1979) and [[Newark Orioles]] (1983-1987) of the [[New York–Penn League]], the [[Newark Barge Bandits]] (1995-1996) of the [[North Atlantic League]] and the [[Newark Raptors]] (1998-2005) of the [[New York Collegiate Baseball League]].<ref name="PGCBL">[http://pgcbl.com/news/index.html?article_id=432 Perfect Game Collegiate Baseball League - Colburn Park], Retrieved Sep. 16, 2017.</ref> It opened in 1968 and seats 2,000 people.<ref>[http://www.ballparkreviews.com/newarkny/newark.htm BallparkReviews.com]</ref>

