{{infobox country at games | NOC = ERI | NOCname = [[Eritrean National Olympic Committee]] | games = Summer Olympics | year = 2004 | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = | location = [[Athens]] | competitors = '''4''' | sports = 1 | flagbearer = [[Yonas Kifle]] | rank = 71 | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 1 | officials = | appearances = auto | app_begin_year = 2000 | app_end_year = | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | seealso = {{flaglink|Ethiopia|variant=1991|at the Olympics}} (1956–1992) }}
'''[[Eritrea]]''' competed at the '''[[2004 Summer Olympics]]''' in [[Athens]], [[Greece]], from 13 to 29 August 2004. The nation won its first Olympic medal ever at these Games, in its second appearance.
