{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2014}} {{Infobox National handball team | Name = Faroe Islands | type = M | Badge = Faroe handball federation.png | Nickname = | Association = Hondboltsamband Føroya | Coach = Sonni Larsen | Captain = | Most caps = | Most goals = | pattern_la1 = | pattern_la2 = }} The '''Faroe Islands national handball team''' is the national [[handball]] team of [[Faroe Islands]] and is controlled by the Hondboltsamband Foroya.
In June 2015 the team competed in the [[2015 IHF Emerging Nations Championship]], the Faroese team won the championship.<ref name="Champions">{{cite web|url=http://kvf.fo/greinar/2015/06/26/foroyar-vunnu-i-kosovo|title=Føroyar vunnu í Kosovo|last=Frederiksen|first=Leivur|date=26 June 2015|publisher=Kringvarp Føroya|language=Faroese|accessdate=27 June 2015}}</ref> In June 2017 the team competed in the [[2017 IHF Emerging Nations Championship]], and again they won the championship.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://kvf.fo/greinar/2017/06/18/foroyar-vunnu-altjoda-kapping |title=Føroyar vunnu altjóða kapping |last1=Frederiksen |first1=Leivur |last2= |first2= |date=18 June 2017 |work= |publisher=Kringvarp Føroya |accessdate=19 June 2017}}</ref>
