'''Palmar de Junco''' is where in 1874 the first official game of [[Baseball in Cuba|Cuban baseball]] was played.  It was once owned by the [[del Junco]] family.  It is located at Calzada Esteban between Monserrate and San Ignacio streets in the neighborhood of [[Pueblo Nuevo, Matanzas]], [[Cuba]].

==References==
* ''Historia del Palmar de Junco'', Israel M. Moliner (Matanzas, Cuba: {{not a typo|Reimpresion}} de Museo, 1960)

